    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The view "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Common.uvw_GetDatabaseEnvironmentServerAndDatabaseName",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to provide metadata about the SQL Server instance and the database environment. It returns three columns: the server instance name, the database name, and a classification of the environment as either 'QA' or 'PROD'. This classification is determined by checking if the server name contains the substring 'EC3SQLPROD'. If it does, the environment is labeled as 'PROD'; otherwise, it defaults to 'QA'."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity level of this view is low. It involves a straightforward selection of server and database metadata using system functions ("
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "@@SERVERNAME",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "DB_NAME()",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ") and a simple conditional logic using "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "CASE",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "PATINDEX",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " to determine the environment. There are no joins, subqueries, or complex calculations involved."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
